[[File:Crow Foot by DF Barry.jpg|thumb|Crow Foot]]

'''Crow Foot''' (1873 – December 15, 1890) was the son of [[Sitting Bull]] of the [[Lakota people|Lakota]]. His mother was either Seen by Her Nation or Four Robes. He had sisters named Standing Holy and Lodge; he also had brothers named Henry, Little Soldier, Red Scout, and Theodore.

In 1881 he participated alongside his father in the surrender at [[Fort Buford]]. Crow Foot was killed along with his father on December 15, 1890, by a group of [[Indian agent]]s.

