A '''Faroese Dane''' is a resident of [[Denmark]] with a [[Faroese Islanders|Faroese]] ethnic background.

==Statistics==
In 2006, 21,687 people of Faroese descent were recorded in Denmark, a figure almost half the population of the [[Faroe Islands]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://politiken.dk/indland/article166953.ece | title=Færøske unge flygter til Danmark | publisher=Politiken | date=30 August 2006 | accessdate=7 November 2015 | language=Danish}}</ref>

On average each year, not fewer than 240 Faroese move to Denmark from Faroe Islands, which is about 0.5% of the Faroese population.{{Citation needed|date=April 2012}}

